data.description: Located between Belton and Stillhouse Lakes in a small town minutes from shopping in Harker Heights, is an ideal single-story home on nearly 3 acres. This rare, large property in Nolanville is an excellent buy with an $8,000 SELLER CREDIT to reduce closing costs or buy down interest for a lower payment! The large pasture has a barn with electric and water, ideal for those with horses, or convert to RV storage, woodworking or entertainment area. Enclosed 12'x20' storage shed with concrete at barn. Lots of room for pool, additions or guest house. No HOA! Home upgrades include a water softener, ROWPU under sink, surround sound wiring, smart devices/doorbell, and new rear windows, and craftsman-style crown moulding. The large kitchen has abundant cabinets and counter space, with two pantries. The rear of the property is lined with mature trees so that you have all the benefits of nature and privacy. This spacious property has an acre front yard, and a large fenced backyard separate from the fenced pasture. No immediate neighbors in the back or side. Your commute to the cities is simple in this centrally located quiet town, yet just 3 minutes down the road you'll find large convenience stores, gas stations, and restaurants. 10 minutes to I-35 and Belton, 15 minutes to Temple. The home is vacant and move-in ready so schedule to come see today! Don't miss this ideal Central Texas homestead.
